@node "Introduction" "Introduction to ZLibExample"
@next "Introduction"
@prev "Introduction"

@{JCENTER}@{b}@{u}Introduction@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}ZLibExample@{ub} is a simple example which makes use of zlib.library V3+ by Achim Stegemann.
The first version I made was for PowerD. But for some unknown reason the PPC instructions still crash.
So I converted da whole bizznizz to StormC V4. Now even the WOS version works great.

ZLibExample only works from the CLI and has the following arguments:
@{JLEFT}
· @{b}SRC@{ub} - Input File
· @{b}DST@{ub} - Output File (it's not so difficult ;)
· @{b}DEC@{ub} - This is the @{i}DECOMPRESS@{ui} option. Use it for unpacking.
· @{b}CHECK@{ub} - Just wanna have a look how much the unpacked file would take ? Use this one.



@endnode

@node "Requirements" "Requirements for ZLibExample"
@next "Requirements"
@prev "Requirements"

@{JCENTER}@{b}@{u}Requirements@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}ZLibExample@{ub} requires an Amiga (or compatible) with zlib.library V3+, asyncio.library V39+.
The WOS version also needs a @{b}PPC@{ub} processor with @{b}WarpOS@{ub} installed.
For larger files you also need @{u}@{b}LOTS@{ub}@{uu} of memory.

@endnode

